# Project folder structure

Use App Router with TypeScript. Keep route files thin; colocate feature code under each route module in `app/(frontend)/`.

## Top level

```
app/                    # routes only
  layout.tsx            # root: fonts, metadata, globals
  (frontend)/           # public site (navbar + footer layout)
  (auth)/               # login, signup
  (admin)/              # admin shell
components/
  ui/                   # shadcn + global shared UI
  magicui/              # Magic UI components
  home/                 # home-only shared pieces (hero, scroll-to-hash)
lib/                    # site-wide utils (nav-links, utils.ts)
public/                 # static assets
```

## Route groups

| Group | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `(frontend)/` | Portfolio pages with `SiteNavbar` + `SiteFooter` |
| `(auth)/` | Auth pages (no site shell) |
| `(admin)/` | Admin layout only |

## Module pattern (`app/(frontend)/<module>/`)

Each feature gets its own folder — same pattern as `about`, `contact`, `github`:

```
app/(frontend)/<module>/
  page.tsx              # thin route (often HashRedirect to /#section)
  components/           # module UI
    <module>-content.tsx    # composer for home scroll sections
    <module>-section.tsx    # main section UI
    forms/                  # form UI (if needed)
    schema/                 # zod schemas (if needed)
  lib/                  # types, mock data, API helpers
  actions/              # server actions (optional)
```

### Examples in this repo

```
about/
  components/about-content.tsx, about-intro.tsx, education-timeline.tsx, social-links.tsx
  lib/education.ts, socials.ts
  page.tsx → redirects to /#about

github/
  components/github-content.tsx, github-section.tsx, github-section-loader.tsx
  lib/github.ts, github-api.ts
  page.tsx → full page at /github

contact/
  components/contact-section.tsx, contact-channels.tsx, forms/contact-form.tsx
  lib/contact-channels.ts
  page.tsx → redirects to /#contact

projects/
  components/project-grid.tsx, project-card.tsx
  lib/mock-projects.ts
  page.tsx → full page at /projects

blog/
  components/blog-list.tsx, blog-card.tsx
  lib/mock-posts.ts
  page.tsx → full page at /blog
```

## Home scroll sections

Single-page sections on `/` compose module content inside `components/home/home-page-sections.tsx`:

```tsx
<section id="about"><AboutContent /></section>
<section id="contact"><ContactSection /></section>
```

Nav hash links: `/#about`, `/#contact`. Full routes: `/github`, `/projects`, `/blog`.

## Naming

- **Files & folders**: `kebab-case` — `github-section.tsx`, `contact-form.tsx`
- **Variables, props, functions**: `camelCase`
- **Types / interfaces**: `PascalCase`
- **React components**: PascalCase export, kebab-case file — `export function GithubSection`

## Imports

- Module code: `@/app/(frontend)/<module>/...`
- Global UI: `@/components/ui/*`, `@/components/magicui/*`
- Site config: `@/lib/nav-links`
- Never put feature UI in `components/ui/`

## Server vs client

- `lib/*-api.ts` — server fetch helpers (no `"use client"`)
- `*-loader.tsx` — async server component that fetches and passes props
- `*-section.tsx` — `"use client"` when using motion/interactivity
- Wrap async loaders in `<Suspense>` from a server parent (`*-content.tsx`)

## Do / Don't

```tsx
// ❌ Feature API inside about/ for github data
// app/(frontend)/about/lib/github-api.ts

// ✅ Own module folder
// app/(frontend)/github/lib/github-api.ts
// app/(frontend)/github/components/github-content.tsx
```
